  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (physical fault gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The pump operates in continuous in vivo deployment across multi-hour surgical procedures, exposing hardware to bearing wear, seal degradation, and motor thermal cycling. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). All validation experiments and simulations assume nominal hardware in perfect operating condition; no fault states are modelled.",
